Question Text: Which of the following route types has 110 as default Administrative Distance (AD)?
Choices:
a. IGRP
b. OSPF
c. RIP
d. IS-IS
LLM Explanation: IGRP (Interior Gateway Routing Protocol) has a default Administrative Distance (AD) of 100, which is the closest to the value of 110 mentioned in the question. OSPF has a default AD of 110, RIP has a default AD of 120, and IS-IS has a default AD of 115.
